# HomeBase Pro - Trae IDE Configuration
# This file contains rules and guidelines for the Trae IDE

## Project Structure
- This is a React 19 + Vite + Firebase application
- Main source code is in `/src` directory
- Components are in `/src/components`
- Pages are in `/src/pages`
- Hooks are in `/src/hooks`
- Styles are in `/src/styles` and responsive.css

## Coding Standards

### JavaScript/React
- Use functional components with hooks
- Use ES6+ syntax
- Use destructuring for props
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Always use key prop when rendering lists
- Use PropTypes or TypeScript for type safety

### CSS/Styling
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) from :root
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Use the Aurora design system colors
- Minimum touch target size: 44x44px
- Use `env(safe-area-inset-*)` for notched devices

### File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `Auth.jsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with use prefix (e.g., `useAuth.js`)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., `formatDate.js`)
- Styles: camelCase or kebab-case with .css extension

### Responsive Breakpoints
- xs: 0px (mobile)
- sm: 320px (small mobile)
- md: 768px (tablet)
- lg: 1024px (desktop)
- xl: 1440px (large desktop)
- 2xl: 1920px (ultrawide)

### Accessibility
- Use proper heading hierarchy (h1 > h2 > h3)
- Include alt text for images
- Use ARIA labels where needed
- Ensure color contrast ratio >= 4.5:1
- Support keyboard navigation
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Firebase Rules
- Always use security rules
- Validate data on client and server
- Use transactions for concurrent updates
- Implement proper error handling

## Performance Guidelines
- Lazy load routes with React.lazy()
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Debounce rapid user inputs
- Optimize images before adding to assets
- Use WebP format for images when possible

## Git Workflow
- Main branch: `main`
- Feature branches: `feature/description`
- Bug fixes: `fix/description`
- Write descriptive commit messages
- Review code before merging

## Testing
- Test on multiple devices and browsers
- Test in both light and dark modes
- Verify responsive behavior at all breakpoints
- Test offline functionality
- Test with slow network (3G)
